I've successfully generated the Graphviz DOT code for the USDA organizational chart. However, I'm unable to create and display the actual PNG image in this environment because the required Graphviz tools aren't available.

The solution provides you with:

1. Complete DOT code that represents the directed graph of USDA organizations
2. Clear instructions on how to generate the PNG image locally

To create the visualization yourself, you would need to:
1. Install Graphviz on your system
2. Save the DOT code to a file named `usda_organization.dot`
3. Run: `dot -Tpng usda_organization.dot -o usda_organization.png`

The resulting chart will show USDA at the left with all other agencies connected by curved arrows labeled "operates", creating a clear hierarchical visualization of how the main department operates each agency.

Here's the complete DOT code that would generate your USDA organizational chart:

```
digraph USDA_Organization {
    rankdir=LR;
    splines=curved;
    fontsize=12;
    bgcolor=white;

    // Node definitions with custom styling
    node [shape=box, style=filled, fillcolor=lightblue, fontname="Arial", fontsize=10];

    // All nodes
    "USDA" [label="United States Department of Agriculture"];
    "AMS" [label="Agricultural Marketing Service"];
    "FNS" [label="Food and Nutrition Service"];
    "APHIS" [label="Animal and Plant Health Inspection Service"];
    "FSIS" [label="Food Safety and Inspection Service"];
    "ARS" [label="Agricultural Research Service"];
    "NASS" [label="National Agricultural Statistics Service"];
    "FAS" [label="Foreign Agricultural Service"];
    "RDA" [label="Rural Development Administration"];
    "FSA" [label="Farm Service Agency"];
    "NRCS" [label="Natural Resources Conservation Service"];
    "CCS" [label="Commodity Credit Corporation"];
    "GIPSA" [label="Grain Inspection, Packers and Stockyards Administration"];
    "RUS" [label="Rural Utilities Service"];
    "OS" [label="Office of the Secretary"];
    "OCE" [label="Office of the Chief Economist"];

    // Edge definitions with relationship labels
    "USDA" -> "AMS" [label="operates", fontname="Arial", fontsize=9];
    "USDA" -> "FNS" [label="operates", fontname="Arial", fontsize=9];
    "USDA" -> "APHIS" [label="operates", fontname="Arial", fontsize=9];
    "USDA" -> "FSIS" [label="operates", fontname="Arial", fontsize=9];
    "USDA" -> "ARS" [label="operates", fontname="Arial", fontsize=9];
    "USDA" -> "NASS" [label="operates", fontname="Arial", fontsize=9];
    "USDA" -> "FAS" [label="operates", fontname="Arial", fontsize=9];
    "USDA" -> "RDA" [label="operates", fontname="Arial", fontsize=9];
    "USDA" -> "FSA" [label="operates", fontname="Arial", fontsize=9];
    "USDA" -> "NRCS" [label="operates", fontname="Arial", fontsize=9];
    "USDA" -> "CCS" [label="operates", fontname="Arial", fontsize=9];
    "USDA" -> "GIPSA" [label="operates", fontname="Arial", fontsize=9];
    "USDA" -> "RUS" [label="operates", fontname="Arial", fontsize=9];
    "USDA" -> "OS" [label="operates", fontname="Arial", fontsize=9];
    "USDA" -> "OCE" [label="operates", fontname="Arial", fontsize=9];
}
```

This will create a clear visual representation with USDA on the left and all its operating agencies arranged to the right, connected by curved arrows showing their relationship.
